    • Method Detail

      • checkConflict

        public void checkConflict(Activity possibleConflictingActivity)
                   throws edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.course.ConflictException
        Tests whether each meeting day is the same. If not the same, returns nothing. Else checks whether the start time of one activity is less than or equal to the beginning of another activity. It also checks whether the end time of the latter activity is greater or equal to the start time of the formal activity. Thus, if the above conditions are true,there is an overlap. As a result, the method throws a Conflict exception
        Specified by:
        checkConflict in interface edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.course.Conflict
        Parameters:
        possibleConflictingActivity - a possible activity object that might interfere in terms of days and timings
        Throws:
        edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.course.ConflictException - checked exception thrown if start or end time of any activity are the same if any of the meeting day is the same
